<a name="own"></a>
<h2>Own a Family Tree!</h2>

<p>
<ul>
<li>If you have not yet done so, Sign In, or Login by entering your login and password 
in the upper right corner of your screen.<br>
<li>Follow the Go to your Family Tree link in the upper left corner of your screen.<br>
<li>Click your Family Tree name.<br>
<li>Enter your Family Name in the Create a new Family Tree box, agree to the See Our Family Policy by ticking the appropriate box, and hit the create this Family Tree button
<li>Choose a default language (your Family Tree users will be able to change their viewing language as they go), a date format and a title for your Family Tree (in your own language if you wish to do so), and hit the create this Family Tree button
<li>You will be able to return to the following screen anytime you want by following the update link in your Family Tree view (Go to your Family Tree)
<li>The participant list should be initially empty, but you may invite new participants by entering their email addresses in the invitation section (5 free spots for new guests will be available anytime you go back the Family Tree update screen)
<li>As participants Sign In and join your Family Tree you will see them appear in the Participants list
<li>Make them Administrators (able to add/update information to your Family Tree) by moving them up the participants list under Administrators (select the person and click the up link)
<li>Remove them by clicking the delete link
</ul>
</p>

<p>
Participants to your Family Tree are those able to access the information. These are independent from you the people you present in your Family Tree (your relatives).
</p>

